"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857739","Home Office","false","2018-03-16","<p>The Home Office has allocated initial funding of £200,000 for this first year of the new national online hate crime hub. The police report that a caseload of around 1,500 incident reports per year, based on a previous pilot, gives an indication of the potential caseload for the new hub, although this figure will vary based on a number of factors including proactive activity by the police to reach out to communities.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","131641","2018-03-16T12:39:23.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857739/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857739/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857739/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-08","National Online Hate Crime Hub","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the number of cases that will be submitted to the National Online and Hate Crime Hub in the first year of its operation.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","131640"
