"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857824","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-16","<p>The intent to dispose of Ministry of Defence Caledonia was included in the Department's estate optimisation announcement 'A Better Defence Estate' in November 2016. The estimated disposal date is 2022. The future use of the site is a matter for the new owner, but we will work with Local Authorities and relevant stakeholders to ensure the disposal provides the best outcome for Defence and the local community.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-03-16T13:31:27.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857824/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857824/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857824/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-08","MOD Caledonia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has for the future of Caledonia base in Rosyth.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","131725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857825","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-15","<p>The Department is committed to recruiting around 200 Community Partners and is actively doing so. There are Community Partners in place in every Jobcentre Plus District. 116 Community Partners are currently in post and 38 others have accepted offers of employment. For all remaining posts recruitment is ongoing.</p><p> </p><p>Disability Employment Advisors have also been recruited across the Jobcentre Plus network. As at February 2018, there are 470 full time equivalent DEAs with an actual headcount above 500 when taking account of part time and dual role workers.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-03-15T13:43:46.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857825/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857825/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857825/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-08","Department for Work and Pensions: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the recruitment targets set out in her Department's paper Improving Lives: The Future of Work, Health and Disability, what progress she has made on recruiting (a) Community Partners and (b) Disability Employment Advisers.","false","Biography information for Stephen Lloyd","Eastbourne","Stephen Lloyd","131726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857826","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-16","<p>Military Working Dogs (MWD) provide an invaluable service to our troops, and every effort is made to rehome them at the end of their service life. The Ministry of Defence's approach to rehoming is in accordance with the Association of Dogs and Cats Homes Code of Practice and is consistent with that taken by high profile, well respected animal charities.</p><p>Decisions are taken following an extensive assessment of the dogs and any potential new home. We seek to maximise the number that can be rehomed, including through work with animal charities and external behavioural experts.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-03-16T13:35:10.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857826/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857826/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857826/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-08","Armed Forces: Dogs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to reduce the number of euthanized military working dogs.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","131727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857827","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-16","<p>We have recently announced a 24-hour mental health helpline for veterans and their families provided by the charity Combat Stress; the freephone number is 0800 138 1619.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-03-16T14:54:03.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857827/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857827/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/857827/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-08","Veterans: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to extend the armed forces mental health helpline service to veterans.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","131728"
