/td><td><p><strong>483</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><ol><li>Data source: Single Individualised Learner Record.</li><li>Within the Individualised Learner Record, providers can record the start date, planned end date, and actual end date for each apprenticeship record.</li><li>Actual end date is only recorded for learners who have reached the end of their programme, or those who have withdrawn early.</li><li>This calculation only includes those learners who have completed their programme in 2016/17.</li><li>Some learners can complete their programme in a shorter time due to prior learning.</li><li>Some learners take longer than expected due to planned breaks in learning.</li><li>A small number of learners from the Employer Outcome Pilot are not included in this calculation</li></ol>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-03-13T15:59:49.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856974/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856974/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856974/answer","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856974/answer/previousversion/46691","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856974/answer/previousversion/46691",,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-07","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average length of time was for an apprenticeship programme undertaken by (a) women and (b) men in each sector subject area in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","131486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856975","Treasury","false","2018-03-12","<p>The government is determined that everyone who is entitled to the National Minimum and Living Wage (NMW) receives it. Anyone who feels they have been underpaid NMW should contact the Acas helpline on 0300 123 1100. HMRC (HM Revenue &amp; Customs) review all complaints that are referred to them.</p><p> </p><p>In 2016-17 HMRC closed 78 NMW investigations where NMW arrears were identified and that were recorded in relation to apprentices. The 75 male and 158 female workers affected would have been a mix of apprentices and regular workers. HMRC are unable to provide a separate breakdown on how many of these workers were apprentices, or to provide in year enforcement data for 2017-18.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC does not record statistics on complaints or investigations by reference to countries of the United Kingdom, Government regions, constituencies or counties.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","131489","2018-03-12T15:40:30.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856975/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856975/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856975/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-07","Apprentices: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many (a) male and (b) female apprentices were paid less than the minimum wage in (i) the North East and (ii) the UK in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","131487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856976","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-21","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answers to PQ127351 and PQ127354 given on 14<sup>th</sup> March 2018 and the answer to PQ127353 given on 21<sup>st</sup> March.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-21T14:43:00.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856976/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856976/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856976/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-07","Cabinet Office: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he plans to answer Question 127351, Question 127353, and Question 127354, tabled on 7 February 2018 by the hon. Member for Manchester Gorton.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","131488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856977","Treasury","false","2018-03-12","<p>The government is determined that everyone who is entitled to the National Minimum and Living Wage (NMW) receives it. Anyone who feels they have been underpaid NMW should contact the Acas helpline on 0300 123 1100. HMRC (HM Revenue &amp; Customs) review all complaints that are referred to them.</p><p> </p><p>In 2016-17 HMRC closed 78 NMW investigations where NMW arrears were identified and that were recorded in relation to apprentices. The 75 male and 158 female workers affected would have been a mix of apprentices and regular workers. HMRC are unable to provide a separate breakdown on how many of these workers were apprentices, or to provide in year enforcement data for 2017-18.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC does not record statistics on complaints or investigations by reference to countries of the United Kingdom, Government regions, constituencies or counties.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","131487","2018-03-12T15:40:30.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856977/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856977/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856977/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-07","Apprentices: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many companies in (a) the North East and (b) the UK are paying less than the minimum wage for apprenticeship programmes.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","131489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856978","Department for Education","false","2018-03-12","<p>To drive up apprenticeships among underrepresented groups, including black, Asian and minority ethnic individuals, last month we launched a new partnership with five major cities in England, supported by city Mayors, to ensure apprenticeships are accessible to individuals from all backgrounds.</p><p> </p><p>Our Apprenticeship Diversity Champions Network, now comprised of over 40 employers, continues to influence the behaviour of other employers to support more people from underrepresented groups, including those with disabilities, women, and members of black, Asian and minority ethnic communities, to access apprenticeships.</p><p> </p><p>We celebrated National Apprenticeship in 5-9 March, celebrating the positive impact apprenticeships have on individuals, businesses and the wider economy.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","131491","2018-03-12T17:23:40.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856978/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856978/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856978/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-07","Apprentices: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent steps his Department has taken to encourage apprenticeship uptake by people who are from a BAME background.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","131490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856979","Department for Education","false","2018-03-12","<p>To drive up apprenticeships among underrepresented groups, including black, Asian and minority ethnic individuals, last month we launched a new partnership with five major cities in England, supported by city Mayors, to ensure apprenticeships are accessible to individuals from all backgrounds.</p><p> </p><p>Our Apprenticeship Diversity Champions Network, now comprised of over 40 employers, continues to influence the behaviour of other employers to support more people from underrepresented groups, including those with disabilities, women, and members of black, Asian and minority ethnic communities, to access apprenticeships.</p><p> </p><p>We celebrated National Apprenticeship in 5-9 March, celebrating the positive impact apprenticeships have on individuals, businesses and the wider economy.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","131490","2018-03-12T17:23:40.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856979/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856979/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-07","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent steps his Department has taken to encourage apprenticeship uptake by people who are aged over 45.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","131491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856980","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-12","<p>We would encourage employers to exercise common sense and consider the advice given by agencies such as the Met Office on travelling in such adverse conditions.</p><p>Employers should consider their legal obligations under the Health and Safety at Work etc. Act, if asking employees to travel for work.</p><p>Guidance for driving at work can be found in HSE’s leaflet: INDG382 Driving for Work, <a href="http://www.hse.gov.uk/pubns/indg382.pdf" target="_blank">www.hse.gov.uk/pubns/indg382.pdf</a></p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-03-12T14:27:39.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856980/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856980/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856980/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-03-07","Conditions of Employment: Weather","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the Government's policy is on employers requesting workers to travel into work during a red weather warning.","false","Biography information for Ged Killen","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Ged Killen","131492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856981","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-12","<p>BEIS does not collect information on employers requiring staff to travel into work during a red weather warning.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-03-12T14:28:00.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856981/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856981/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856981/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-03-07","Conditions of Employment: Weather","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what information his Department holds on employers requiring staff to travel into work during a red weather warning; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ged Killen","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Ged Killen","131493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856982","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-12","<p>Employers should look kindly on workers who follow official guidance not to travel and treat them in good faith. I would encourage employers to come to a reasonable solution on leave that is fair to employees and right for their business.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-03-12T16:26:31.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856982/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856982/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-03-07","Conditions of Employment: Weather","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he make an assessment of the potential merits of extending employment rights to allow employees take leave during a red weather alert.","false","Biography information for Ged Killen","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Ged Killen","131494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856983","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-12","<p>Since January 2016 Highways England has had no new contracts with Carillion. The Department has not awarded any High Speed Two contracts to Carillion.</p><p> </p><p>However, in July 2017 two Main Works Civils lots were let to a Joint Venture made up of Carillion, Eiffage and Kier (CEK JV). The Contract type entered into with the CEK JV was a NEC Option C with open book provisions.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-03-12T16:14:40.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856983/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/856983/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-03-07","Department for Transport: Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer 6 March 2018 to Question 130560 on Department of Transport: Carillion, which of his Department's Arms Length Bodies' contracts with Carillion since January 2016 were done with Open Book Contract Management.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","131495"
